\citation{dwave:solver_properties_all}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {Study~2: QPU decomposition benchmark (10--1{,}000 plots).} Three full-span QPU methods with Gurobi decomposed baselines (dashed, *): Multilevel(10), CQM-First, Coordinated. \emph  {Left (Runtime):} Gurobi full-problem: 0.007--0.27\,s. Multilevel(10): 14--1{,}633\,s; CQM-First: 7--3{,}495\,s (embedding 80+\%). All Gurobi decomposed baselines complete in ${<}10$\,s. \emph  {Middle (Absolute Gap):} Multilevel(10): 0.09--0.17, zero violations. CQM-First: 0.007--0.17, zero violations. Coordinated: raw 0.003--0.14 but 1--23 one-hot violations; healed gap rises substantially. Gurobi decomposed: Multilevel(10)* and Coordinated* recover gap ${\sim }10^{-3}$ (healed). \emph  {Right (Gap + Violations):} Coordinated violations escalate 1$\to $23 across scales, inflating its raw objective. Multilevel(10) and CQM-First maintain zero violations at all scales. }}{5}{}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:qpu_comprehensive}{{2}{5}{}{figure.2}{}}
\newlabel{fig:qpu_comprehensive@cref}{{[figure][2][]2}{[1][4][]5}{}{}{}}
